If the solvent subject to § 770.5 is composed of only one (1) VOC, the vapor pressure shall be determined by ASTM Method D-2879-86 or from a published source such as: Boublik, T., V. Fried and E. Hala, “The Vapor Pressure of Pure Substances,” Elsevier
        Scientific Publishing Company, New York (1973), or Perry’s Chemical Engineer’s Handbook, McGraw-Hill Book Company (1984), or CRC Handbook of Chemistry and Physics, Chemical Rubber Publishing Company (1986-87), or Lange’s Handbook of Chemistry,
        John A. Dean, editor, McGraw-Hill Book Company (1985);
